{"add":{"doc":{"id":"26a1305c439d0a77c6027197d4ad1ab6e64f2d8f1c0632fa734986e51fb56ebb","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Design_conlang.png/100px-Design_conlang.png","previous":[],"after":["A planned or constructed language—known colloquially or informally as a conlang—is a language whose phonology, grammar, and/or vocabulary have been consciously devised by an individual or group, instead of having evolved naturally. There are many possible reasons to create a constructed language: to ease human communication (see international auxiliary language and code); to bring fiction or an associated constructed world to life; linguistic experimentation; artistic creation; and language games."]}}}